3 m spacing of en echelon breaks with some small minor cracks in between; north-south on both sides of road.
Crack trend 000.
Fractures here in a 3 m wide zone. Fractures are oriented 005.

Single crack across compacted soil and roadway trends 325 to 330.

Small hairline cracks across compacted soil trail. On trend with the middle zone to north and south.
Approximately on InSAR trend, however, distinctive fractures in the trail are not observable. There are many desiccation cracks.

Small fracture set crossing compacted dirt path and extending both north and south a bit into the natural soil although it's difficult to follow in the tall grass on either side. Primarily extensional, general fracture trend is about 330. No clear en echelon trend, there may be a right step. Fracture opening about 1 to 2 cm.
Left stepping en echelon cracks with 1-2 cm opening approx. perpendicular to fault trend.
Small fracture crossing compacted dirt path on broad east facing slope. Appears primarily tensional; trend equals 330.
Minor cracks parallel to traces A and C.
Single N38W crack ~ 1 cm of extension 10 m long.
Congress Valley Road where UAVSAR suggests possible location of deformation. Several fresh cracks cross the asphalt road; most prominent crack trends N15W; very small right-lateral component, ~1 mm.
Sunset Road at end of public access. Cracks across road trend N50W. Water meter box recently dug up - new repair? Another water meter box has lid popping up, related to earthquake?
Driveway shows distributed cracking where lineament crosses; no clear tectonic signal, but there is fresh damage.
Curb in Stonebridge Court is damaged and very small left-lateral offset. Cracks continue across asphalt to south (trend N24W). Asphalt pulled away, 3 cm opening. Multiple curbs fractured.
Many cracks in asphalt street. Most look preexisting with no obvious preferred orientation but have opened. Permissible RL offset at driveway curb joint. Fresh cracking in cement driveway trends 338.
Fresh curb cracks in front of house at curb joint, 20mm right-lateral.
Driveway cracks and en echelon cracks across road. Garage door recently removed and has temporary repair. Curb and asphalt popped up.
Fresh cracking in cement sidewalk and driveway. Crack trends N17W.

Intersection of Alpine Court and Twin Oaks; damaged curb. Crossing intersection heading south is zone of fresh left-stepping en echelon cracks amid many old random cracks in asphalt. House at Alpine Court shows minor damage of garage and cracks through driveway pavement.
Compressional pavement damage . Vertical scarp <5 cm. Compiler note: uptrhown side inferred from photo.
Curb on south side of street shows about 3 mm right-lateral. Crack trends N11E.

Alpine Court. Two cracks in curb on north side of street show small right-lateral, about 1 cm each. Cracks are 93 cm apart. Eastern crack trends N16E, western crack trends N5E. Other curb cracks and damage occur within a zone about 20 m wide, including another curb crack with about 8 mm right-lateral, crack trends N4W. Left-stepping en echelon zone of cracks crosses street to the south. Zone trends N22W.

Several large north-south extensional cracks on northern embankment of small resevoir. On-trend with zone to north, but not continuous with them. Possibly related to fault movement, accentuated by response of artificial fill?  No further cracks found on south side of reservoir.
One main crack with extension. Several minor cracks over ~10-wide zone.
Purely a tension crack, might be shaking related. Represents the south end of subsidiary alignment of fractures.
>10-meter-long zone of cracks (including two left-stepping en echelon) along west side of road, subparallel to and east of "main" zone.
North end of ~10-m-long zone of cracks along side of road.
Broad zone of north-south oriented fractures, small displacement (1-3 mm). Zone consists of 4-6 cracks over ~20-m-wide interval.
Two strands crossing east-west dirt road. One with 1 cm opening, 0.5 cm right-lateral.
~20 m long zone of cracks crossing from vines toward road intersection. Trend ~345-350. 3mm right-lateral.
Prominent, open fractures forming polygonal-type pattern through two vineyard rows. 0.5cm extension with some left-lateral.
Marks eastern side of distributed zone (~20 m wide) cutting across road.
Northwest end of zone. Multiple strands crossing north-south dirt road at low angle, entering vineyard.
Minor ground cracking and en echelon break 1 m-long; left stepping; more poorly expressed than surface ruptures observations immediately to the north.
Several meter-wide zone crossing east-west dirt road. <1 cm openings; possibly mm of right-lateral.
Continuation of small fractures, minimal if any offset.

Possibly right-lateral offset of tire track 0.5 inches. Cracks are fresh, distinguishable from dessiccation cracking, and continuous up to about 10 ft in length.

Fracture in pavement. All cracks are parallel to road; no indication of displacement at all.

Short alignment of extensional cracks on south hillslope embankment (transverse to slope) --didn't continue on upper or lower surfaces. Cracks in roadway don't appear to be fresh. No apparent offset of highway lines.
Tiny crack from pavement through dirt. No offset. No other apparent surface rupture in this area.
Minor extensional cracks. Vaguely left-stepping across road, oblique to creek, ~5-10 m from creek.  Trend ~314 (Small fractures that do not appear aligned to. previous fractures).
Small extensional north-south trending crack, several meters long, crossing dirt road.
North-south cracks along roadside - runs between newly planted trees beneath thin irrigation hose. Possibly related to buried water line?
2 m long extensional crack crosses into dirt road with 339 trend; can't trace into field about 10 m west of creek.
Grid-like (polygonal) pattern of open cracks down dirt road with suggestion of 1- 2mm right-lateral in places. Can't trace into vines (recently plowed) to west or into roadside to east.

West edge of dip in road at recent landslide pavement patch 100 ft. to east; no recent cracking.

Extensional crack across road about 5 cm open; downslope side of road wider. Up 2 in. to south and open 2 ft. deep on upslope side of road.

3-6 cm extension fracture.

Fractures in paved road.
Several open cracks in very steep driveway. Open toward side slope and downslope of driveway. Many are pre-existing. Cracks do not extend to soil.

Crack perpendicular across driveway. No cracking in adjacent soil. No lateral movement along edge of asphalt. Minor driveway parallel crack at road. Irregular trend closed at east end. Many pre-existing cracks in road do not look fresh.
Large driveway fracture and house with extensive structural damage.
Dry Creek Road.
Pre-existing crack nearly perpendicular across Dry Creek Road. Open <1 cm. Scissored vertical <1 cm. Weeds growing in crack at both ends. No lateral offset on lane striping.
Four linear cracks with primarily left stepping, en echelon traces. General trend 293. Can only trace for 8 m north.

Crack almost perpendicular to road and can be traced to north into natural ground. Cannot trace completely across road, may actually tie into cracks that are parallel to road. May be shaking related. Orientation of cracks is 173.
Two short left stepping cracks in compacted road surface. Cannot clearly trace into native dirt and cannot extend across road into vineyard to south. Orientation of individual cracks is 272.

Hairline fracture across dirt road, can be extended to the north west and south east a few meters into the soil. Trend 113.
Minor tenting across driveway along pre-existing cracks. Do not extend into soil. No lateral offset. Other similar features along this driveway.

Many pre-existing cracks in old asphalt. Some open. Longest cracks are related to creep into drainage ditch adjacent to road. Many other irregular cracks.

Apparent 1 cm left-lateral offset of double yellow and white lane lines. Many irregular cracks in driveway. Uncertain origin but difficult to understand as tectonic based on distance from observed rupture.

Fractures in pavement and soil appear to be mostly horizontal. Zone of separation up to 25 ft. Eastern most cracking along roadway. Mostly horizontal separation.

Zone of cracks across asphalt seem to be related to slumping into adjacent drainage ditch. Quite extensive, about 50 m long, parallel to the roadway and it seems to be related to weak pavement. Direction roughly N45W.
Deformation on Partrick Rd. Cracks show predominantly horizontal separation.

Open crack across street 3.5 cm. Extends across soil and beneath house into backyard. Foundation damaged. No lateral displacement observed. Crack along crest of local ridgeline, possibly gravity related.
Cracks on bedrock fault.

Cracking in the street that extended across the whole paved section and into the soil adjacent, projecting under the house along ~335 degrees. No cracking or deformation of the property to the south was apparent.

On trend with cracks in street and through house. Crack open 2 cm in dirt, not continuous to tank access road. Opening in downslope direction. Right-lateral offset ~ 2 cm in v-ditch up slope of house. Possibly gravity related.

Observed two co-linear cracks in soil about 2 m apart with ~1-2.5 cm of separation. These trended ~325 degrees and did not have any apparent lateral or vertical displacement. One of the panels of the fence had also pulled apart by about 1.5 inches.
